# UI & Forms

## Components

- Build UI from shadcn primitives in `src/components/ui`; compose app widgets in `src/components/app`.
- Add new shadcn components with the CLI (`pnpm dlx shadcn@latest add <name>`); do not hand-roll them.
- Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` to merge classes. Use semantic design tokens
  (`bg-background`, `text-muted-foreground`, `border`, etc.), never hard-coded hex in JSX.
- Icons come from `lucide-react`.

## Forms (react-hook-form + zod)

- Use `useForm<Input, unknown, Output>({ resolver: zodResolver(schema) })`.
- **Keep the form schema's input and output types identical** (e.g. keep optional fields as
  `string | undefined`, do not `.transform()` to `null`). Apply `null`/shape transforms in the
  `create*/update*` schemas used by the server function instead — otherwise shadcn `FormField`
  control types break.

## Accessibility

- Every interactive element is keyboard reachable and labelled. Prefer semantic elements;
  only use ARIA roles for genuinely custom widgets and justify with a `biome-ignore`.
